      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from class: org.locationtech.jts.geom.Geometry
        Tests whether this geometry is structurally and numerically equal to a given Object. If the argument Object is not a Geometry, the result is false. Otherwise, the result is computed using Geometry.equalsExact(Geometry).

        This method is provided to fulfill the Java contract for value-based object equality. In conjunction with Geometry.hashCode() it provides semantics which are most useful for using Geometrys as keys and values in Java collections.

        Note that to produce the expected result the input geometries should be in normal form. It is the caller's responsibility to perform this where required (using Geometry.norm() or Geometry.normalize() as appropriate).

        Overrides:
        equals in class org.locationtech.jts.geom.Geometry
        Parameters:
        o - the Object to compare
        Returns:
        true if this geometry is exactly equal to the argument
        See Also:
        Geometry.equalsExact(Geometry), Geometry.hashCode(), Geometry.norm(), Geometry.normalize()
